was growing faster than you

59:05.810 --> 59:08.612
and sort of crowding you out.

59:08.678 --> 59:11.115
You weren't developing properly.

59:11.181 --> 59:15.052
So, we decided
to have a procedure

59:15.119 --> 59:17.487
where you were both born early

59:17.554 --> 59:22.092
and...the doctors didn't
think you were gonna live.

59:22.159 --> 59:24.061
So, um..

59:28.933 --> 59:32.569
I remember you were so tiny.

59:32.636 --> 59:34.939
Not even two pounds.

59:38.642 --> 59:42.479
I remember the doctors
putting you in this glass box

59:42.546 --> 59:47.952
with tubes coming out
everywhere. And, um..

59:49.086 --> 59:54.058
Uh, tsk, then they..

59:54.124 --> 59:55.492
started tellin' us

59:55.559 --> 59:59.763
about all these
surgeries that you'd need

59:59.830 --> 01:00:01.866
and about how you'd be on pills
for the rest of your life.

01:00:01.932 --> 01:00:04.734
How your gut didn't develop.

01:00:04.801 --> 01:00:07.872
They didn't know if anything
would be able fix it.

01:00:09.739 --> 01:00:11.008
And..

01:00:11.909 --> 01:00:13.844
Sean, we wanted nothing more..

01:00:14.678 --> 01:00:16.280
...than to help you.

01:00:18.348 --> 01:00:20.050
And all that stuff
you would need

01:00:20.117 --> 01:00:22.319
was way more than
we could afford.

01:00:28.058 --> 01:00:30.027
Uh, then a social worker
came in

01:00:30.094 --> 01:00:32.930
and said that
there are these couples.

01:00:32.997 --> 01:00:35.399
They could take a preemie.

01:00:35.465 --> 01:00:37.501
They had money and time.

01:00:37.567 --> 01:00:40.570
We knew right away that that was
the best option for you.

01:00:42.072 --> 01:00:44.774
I was so scared that
we were gonna ruin your life

01:00:44.841 --> 01:00:47.444
or, or that you'd die

01:00:47.511 --> 01:00:49.346
because we couldn't..

01:00:49.413 --> 01:00:53.150
...you know, get you
the treatment that you needed.

01:00:53.217 --> 01:00:54.885
So, we looked
at some couples

01:00:54.952 --> 01:00:58.322
and picked a pair of scientists.

01:01:00.557 --> 01:01:04.128
And that, they were older
and really wanted kids

01:01:04.194 --> 01:01:06.596
and they could give you
the treatment you needed.

01:01:08.032 --> 01:01:09.666
Plus, I always thought
that maybe some day

01:01:09.733 --> 01:01:12.069
they could find a way
to make you better.

01:01:14.905 --> 01:01:17.774
You have no idea

01:01:17.841 --> 01:01:21.278
what it means to me, to Paula..

01:01:22.146 --> 01:01:23.780
...to see you healthy.

01:01:23.847 --> 01:01:25.182
And..

01:01:27.051 --> 01:01:28.618
...tss, looking awesome.

01:01:30.587 --> 01:01:32.056
You are a miracle.

01:01:33.290 --> 01:01:35.459
But you guys wanted to keep me.

01:01:35.525 --> 01:01:37.061
Absolutely.

01:01:40.664 --> 01:01:41.999
Yeah.

01:02:47.731 --> 01:02:50.467
I wonder what my friends
are doing right now.

01:02:50.534 --> 01:02:52.702
I bet it's less weird
than this.

01:02:55.639 --> 01:02:57.774
- Hey.
- Hey.

01:02:57.841 --> 01:02:59.109
Hey.

01:03:01.311 --> 01:03:03.313
How are you doing?

01:03:04.448 --> 01:03:05.649
Fine.

01:03:05.715 --> 01:03:09.119
That was kind of
an avalanche, huh?

01:03:10.054 --> 01:03:11.388
Yeah.

01:03:11.455 --> 01:03:13.290
Yeah, you can say that again.

01:03:15.292 --> 01:03:17.761
You know, but it, it was good.

01:03:17.827 --> 01:03:20.030
I, uh, I wanted to meet them.

01:03:20.097 --> 01:03:21.698
So..

01:03:21.765 --> 01:03:24.701
I'm sorry for what I said
about our parents.

01:03:24.768 --> 01:03:27.071
They're not actually that bad.

01:03:28.138 --> 01:03:29.706
No worries.

01:03:30.640 --> 01:03:32.776
Do you like them?

01:03:34.711 --> 01:03:36.046
Yeah.

01:03:37.381 --> 01:03:39.749
Yeah, they're-they're cool.

01:03:42.486 --> 01:03:44.121
They are.

01:03:44.188 --> 01:03:46.223
But, they were kind of

01:03:46.290 --> 01:03:48.925
on their best behavior tonight.

01:03:48.992 --> 01:03:50.760
They're usually
a pain in my ass.

01:03:51.728 --> 01:03:52.762
Well, I mean, I think

01:03:52.829 --> 01:03:55.632
most parents can be
a pain in the ass.

01:03:55.699 --> 01:03:58.034
I know my parents
certainly can be.

01:03:58.102 --> 01:04:00.204
I hate it when you say that.

01:04:00.270 --> 01:04:03.140
Your parents are my parents.

01:04:03.207 --> 01:04:06.543
Those people are,
I don't know..

01:04:06.610 --> 01:04:08.212
...something.

01:04:08.278 --> 01:04:10.280
Yeah, but..

01:04:10.347 --> 01:04:13.583
Chloe, those people
were all I knew.

01:04:15.719 --> 01:04:17.754
They took care of me.

01:04:19.823 --> 01:04:20.990
I know.

01:04:21.057 --> 01:04:22.559
I'm sorry.

01:04:24.128 --> 01:04:26.563
Are you okay?

01:04:26.630 --> 01:04:28.365
No, not really.

01:04:29.733 --> 01:04:31.067
Sorry.

01:04:33.837 --> 01:04:35.605
This is all my fault.

01:04:35.672 --> 01:04:38.074
Actually,
all this is my fault.

01:04:39.976 --> 01:04:41.278
Everything.

01:04:42.679 --> 01:04:46.316
I mean, I-I don't really
see how that's possible.

01:04:46.383 --> 01:04:48.585
They didn't tell you?

01:04:48.652 --> 01:04:50.154
Tell me what?

01:04:52.256 --> 01:04:54.324
The reason you're sick.

01:04:54.391 --> 01:04:55.592
I mean, the reason I was sick

01:04:55.659 --> 01:04:57.494
was 'cause
I didn't develop properly.

01:04:57.561 --> 01:04:58.762
I mean, that-that sort of stuff

01:04:58.828 --> 01:05:01.631
just happens with twins.

01:05:01.698 --> 01:05:03.600
Yeah, but..

01:05:03.667 --> 01:05:05.369
...that was me.

01:05:06.603 --> 01:05:10.374
I was this giant, evil baby
crushing you..

01:05:11.175 --> 01:05:13.210
...not letting you grow.

01:05:14.911 --> 01:05:17.681
They barely saved your life.

01:05:17.747 --> 01:05:20.284
Chloe, I don't think
you did it on purpose.

01:05:20.350 --> 01:05:23.287
You weren't an evil baby.

01:05:24.288 --> 01:05:25.855
If I hadn't..

01:05:25.922 --> 01:05:27.791
...none of this
would've happened..

01:05:29.193 --> 01:05:31.395
...we would've been
a normal family.

01:05:33.330 --> 01:05:34.698
I don't know about normal.

01:05:38.968 --> 01:05:40.837
You'd be happy.

01:05:42.972 --> 01:05:45.775
You know, we can't undo it.

01:05:45.842 --> 01:05:47.177
So..

01:05:48.378 --> 01:05:51.481
You could live with us.

01:05:51.548 --> 01:05:54.551
We could share a room
and, we could surf.

01:05:57.020 --> 01:05:58.222
Seriously.

01:05:58.288 --> 01:06:01.191
Move up here.

01:06:02.459 --> 01:06:05.795
Is it-is it even doable? I..

01:06:05.862 --> 01:06:07.764
Sure it is, I mean..

01:06:07.831 --> 01:06:10.600
I could tell that
they love you and..

01:06:10.667 --> 01:06:12.302
...I love you.

01:06:12.369 --> 01:06:14.404
You're my own brother.

01:06:16.473 --> 01:06:18.174
I love you too, sis.

01:06:20.310 --> 01:06:21.411
Chloe.

01:06:21.478 --> 01:06:23.947
Oh, my God, okay, uh..

01:06:26.516 --> 01:06:28.518
You're the best.
You know that, right?

01:06:29.619 --> 01:06:31.755
I can't wait till
you're up here for good.

01:06:31.821 --> 01:06:32.956
Goodnight.

01:06:33.757 --> 01:06:35.659
Goodnight.

01:06:35.725 --> 01:06:38.628
Wait. How did she interpret
that as a yes?

01:06:44.968 --> 01:06:48.305
Drives eight hours
and sleeps in a parking lot.

01:06:48.372 --> 01:06:50.907
I'm not assuming anything.

01:06:53.543 --> 01:06:55.579
Where're his parents?

01:06:55.645 --> 01:06:57.847
Probably out looking for him.

01:06:57.914 --> 01:06:59.849
Well, clearly not hard enough.

01:07:01.351 --> 01:07:03.320
I'm just saying
it's a crap situation.

01:07:06.490 --> 01:07:08.425
I mean, we should call CPS.

01:07:09.259 --> 01:07:11.261
What?

01:07:11.328 --> 01:07:13.196
- For Sean's sake.
- That's ridiculous.

01:07:13.263 --> 01:07:15.365
They've obviously
put a lot of time and money

01:07:15.432 --> 01:07:16.933
into making him better.

01:07:17.000 --> 01:07:19.803
Doesn't sound like
bad parenting to me.

01:07:19.869 --> 01:07:21.571
Yeah, well,
just because you're rich

01:07:21.638 --> 01:07:23.773
doesn't mean
you're good people.

01:07:25.575 --> 01:07:26.843
How do I rewind?

01:07:29.012 --> 01:07:31.748
I just wanna go home.

01:08:15.459 --> 01:08:16.960
Robert, it's him.

01:08:19.395 --> 01:08:20.997
He says he's gonna
see us tomorrow.

01:08:21.064 --> 01:08:22.131
And?

01:08:22.198 --> 01:08:25.001
And he hopes that
we're having fun.

01:08:27.170 --> 01:08:28.904
Is he on drugs?

01:08:29.939 --> 01:08:31.875
We're gonna find him.

01:08:33.042 --> 01:08:34.978
We're gonna find him.

01:08:38.180 --> 01:08:39.582
- Thank you.
- Mm-hmm.

01:08:39.649 --> 01:08:42.919
Vegan pancakes, can't fake that.

01:08:42.986 --> 01:08:43.953
Not hungry?

01:08:44.020 --> 01:08:45.054
I'm starving because

01:08:45.121 --> 01:08:46.423
they may be weed pancakes.

01:08:46.490 --> 01:08:48.256
I'm tired,
because I didn't sleep

01:08:48.323 --> 01:08:49.626
and I have no idea

01:08:49.693 --> 01:08:51.428
how I'm gonna get home
before my parents.

01:08:51.495 --> 01:08:53.596
Oh, yeah,
and I still need to leave

01:08:53.662 --> 01:08:55.399
without having
Chloe go nuts.

01:08:55.465 --> 01:08:56.600
Ah, not really.

01:08:56.666 --> 01:08:57.701
Maybe it's the drive home?

01:08:57.767 --> 01:08:59.803
Maybe it's the shitty breakfast.

01:08:59.868 --> 01:09:01.505
Thank you.

01:09:01.571 --> 01:09:03.106
Yeah.

01:09:04.474 --> 01:09:06.576
Are you sure
you're alright to drive down?

01:09:06.643 --> 01:09:08.444
Yeah. I'm good.

01:09:08.511 --> 01:09:10.013
Well, Henry and I
can drive down with you

01:09:10.078 --> 01:09:11.848
and one of us can fly back.

01:09:11.915 --> 01:09:15.785
Um, so, taking the one down
is a good plan.

01:09:15.852 --> 01:09:17.987
And, uh, it's,
it's that one there.

01:09:18.054 --> 01:09:20.023
Well, we'll stock you up
with a lots of munchies--

01:09:20.089 --> 01:09:23.091
Or one of us can just go
with you, it's no problem.

01:09:23.158 --> 01:09:25.361
Really, it's okay.
I mean, everything.

01:09:25.429 --> 01:09:28.564
I don't want you to have to
run into my other parents.

01:09:28.631 --> 01:09:31.167
- It would be weird.
- Um..

01:09:31.234 --> 01:09:33.301
Look, it's-it's fine, Sean.

01:09:33.368 --> 01:09:35.604
If-if you're scared
to go home..

01:09:35.671 --> 01:09:39.175
Clearly, this is a,
this is a big deal.

01:09:39.242 --> 01:09:40.577
I mean, are you..

01:09:40.644 --> 01:09:42.178
Are you afraid
of what your dad's gonna do

01:09:42.245 --> 01:09:44.313
when you get home?

01:09:44.380 --> 01:09:48.151
Well, yeah. I mean, if he
finds out, he's gonna flip.

01:09:48.216 --> 01:09:50.819
So will my mom, but..

01:09:50.886 --> 01:09:53.156
Okay. Um..

01:09:53.221 --> 01:09:54.924
Sean, honey..

01:09:57.026 --> 01:10:00.564
- Does your dad beat you?
- What?

01:10:00.630 --> 01:10:02.499
It's okay to talk to us,
we're safe.

01:10:02.566 --> 01:10:05.469
Whatever, whatever
he said to you..

01:10:05.535 --> 01:10:07.504
...we can take care of you.

01:10:07.571 --> 01:10:09.338
We can take care of you.

01:10:09.405 --> 01:10:11.575
You can tell us,
we are safe for you.

01:10:11.641 --> 01:10:13.109
I mean, he, he pushed me once--

01:10:13.176 --> 01:10:14.811
- I-I told you.
- Oh, my God.

01:10:14.878 --> 01:10:17.313
Oh, you-you are more than
welcome to stay here

01:10:17.380 --> 01:10:18.682
for as long as you want,
we are..

01:10:18.748 --> 01:10:20.216
- Totally.
- We're so happy to do that.

01:10:20.283 --> 01:10:22.318
They're never gonna
let me leave now.

01:10:22.385 --> 01:10:24.053
I'm gonna have to be vegan.

01:10:24.120 --> 01:10:25.321
I can't do this.

01:10:25.388 --> 01:10:27.056
We can take care of you.

01:10:27.123 --> 01:10:29.459
We'll figure something out,
for as long as you need.

01:10:30.660 --> 01:10:31.995
Totally.

01:10:34.263 --> 01:10:35.632
I'll grab it.

01:10:37.200 --> 01:10:38.167
Okay, thank you.

01:10:38.234 --> 01:10:39.536
Is that your mother again?

01:10:42.305 --> 01:10:44.641
- Hi.
- Chloe, good morning.

01:10:44.708 --> 01:10:45.675
Is Sean here?

01:10:45.742 --> 01:10:47.010
Uh, how do you know my name?

01:10:47.076 --> 01:10:48.211
Facebook.

01:10:48.277 --> 01:10:50.046
Figures. Uh, Sean?

01:10:50.113 --> 01:10:51.114
No.

01:10:53.717 --> 01:10:55.251
I think that's his parents.

01:10:55.318 --> 01:10:57.220
- Oh, uh..
- Are you okay?

01:10:57.286 --> 01:10:59.589
I never thought I'd say this,
but thank God

01:10:59.656 --> 01:11:01.424
that Val Moreth is here.

01:11:01.491 --> 01:11:02.659
I just have to get out of here

01:11:02.726 --> 01:11:04.060
before anyone finds out
the truth.

01:11:04.127 --> 01:11:05.629
And we'll be okay.

01:11:05.695 --> 01:11:07.864
- I'm okay, I'm okay.
- What's going on?

01:11:07.931 --> 01:11:10.399
- What're you doing here?
- Excuse me.

01:11:10.466 --> 01:11:12.268
- No, I haven't.
- What did you eat?

01:11:12.335 --> 01:11:13.336
Did you check the ingredients?

01:11:13.402 --> 01:11:14.671
Who is this?

01:11:14.738 --> 01:11:16.139
- The da.. Wait, the other dad.
- It's him.

01:11:16.205 --> 01:11:18.675
Sean, Sean..
Are they stressing you out?

01:11:18.742 --> 01:11:19.976
- Um..
- Excuse me?

01:11:20.043 --> 01:11:21.511
- Hi, excuse me, yeah.
- We should go.

01:11:21.578 --> 01:11:22.779
Okay, well, you two listen,
we all know

01:11:22.846 --> 01:11:23.980
happy boys
don't run away from home.

01:11:24.047 --> 01:11:25.749
I-I don't know
who you people are

01:11:25.815 --> 01:11:28.217
but that's a steep assumption.
Let's go, Sean.

01:11:28.284 --> 01:11:31.087
Okay, uh, uh he's only gonna
go if he wants to go.

01:11:31.154 --> 01:11:33.022
And that's exactly
what he just said.

01:11:33.089 --> 01:11:35.124
It's not like
you gave him any option.

01:11:35.191 --> 01:11:36.359
Um..

01:11:36.425 --> 01:11:37.794
You don't have
the right to tell me

01:11:37.861 --> 01:11:39.596
what happens to my son.

01:11:39.663 --> 01:11:41.464
Uh, okay, he's my son too.

01:11:41.531 --> 01:11:43.099
- On what planet?
- Planet Earth.

01:11:43.166 --> 01:11:45.835
- We are his birth parents.
- Yep.

01:11:45.902 --> 01:11:48.004
- Yeah.
- I need a drink.

01:11:48.071 --> 01:11:50.506
I'm so sorry, I lied to Sean
to get him up here.

01:11:50.574 --> 01:11:51.541
Look, I don't care
why he's here.

01:11:51.608 --> 01:11:52.809
Is-is-is that true?

01:11:52.876 --> 01:11:54.544
I mean, are, are you
related to these people?

01:11:54.611 --> 01:11:56.713
I didn't know it
on the drive up.

01:11:56.780 --> 01:11:58.047
I-I didn't-I didn't even know
that Chloe

01:11:58.114 --> 01:11:59.749
was my twin sister,
but yes.

01:11:59.816 --> 01:12:02.151
Like I said, totally my fault.

01:12:02.218 --> 01:12:04.888
You have a twin? You have
a twin, did you know that..

01:12:04.954 --> 01:12:07.691
Sweetheart,
I-I did not know that.

01:12:07.757 --> 01:12:09.258
Well, things didn't
really go as planned.

01:12:09.325 --> 01:12:11.928
- I, I didn't know.
- What're you saying?

01:12:11.995 --> 01:12:13.229
Sean, what're you saying?

01:12:13.296 --> 01:12:15.198
He's saying he wants to stay.

01:12:15.264 --> 01:12:16.700
No, I-I did not say that.

01:12:16.766 --> 01:12:18.635
You said that,
and-and Paula said that.

01:12:18.702 --> 01:12:19.703
I never said that.

01:12:19.769 --> 01:12:22.171
She's not Paula.
She's your mom.

01:12:22.238 --> 01:12:24.808
We-we talked about this
last night, Sean.

01:12:24.874 --> 01:12:27.310
- Are you guys smoking pot?
- Excuse me?

01:12:27.376 --> 01:12:28.477
Yeah, 'cause it smells of pot.

01:12:28.544 --> 01:12:31.781
We love him,
and we want him to stay.

01:12:31.848 --> 01:12:33.116
He shouldn't have left
in the first place.

01:12:33.182 --> 01:12:34.684
Chloe, enough.
You're not helping.

01:12:34.751 --> 01:12:36.820
No, shut up, mom.
You're not helping.

01:12:36.886 --> 01:12:39.155
All of you don't care
what me and Sean want.

01:12:39.222 --> 01:12:41.157
We want to be together.

01:12:41.224 --> 01:12:44.227
I just really wanna hear it
from you, little fish.

01:12:46.095 --> 01:12:48.031
Do you wanna stay?

01:12:49.565 --> 01:12:51.768
Is that why you came?

01:12:55.705 --> 01:12:57.907
It's complicated, mom, I mean..

01:12:57.974 --> 01:13:00.176
Everything changed
this weekend.

01:13:10.119 --> 01:13:11.855
Mom? Mom?
Just lay down here.

01:13:11.921 --> 01:13:13.389
Did you know
anything about this?

01:13:13.456 --> 01:13:14.858
Put your legs up.

01:13:14.924 --> 01:13:16.292
Do you need something?

01:13:16.359 --> 01:13:18.394
Another kick in the gut,
that's what I need.

01:13:18.461 --> 01:13:21.330
Uh, okay. I have, uh,
St. John's wort to calm her

01:13:21.397 --> 01:13:23.332
or chamomile..

01:13:25.101 --> 01:13:27.136
Hey, do you guys want some pot
or something?

01:13:27.203 --> 01:13:28.805
You know what,
that doesn't surprise me.

01:13:28.872 --> 01:13:30.840
Whatever, dad.
I found your joint in the car.

01:13:30.907 --> 01:13:32.742
What? Did you smoke it?

01:13:32.809 --> 01:13:34.177
I can't find it,
I don't, I'm--

01:13:34.243 --> 01:13:35.645
Can-can I get some water,
please?

01:13:35.712 --> 01:13:37.113
- Yeah, Chloe, please.
- Thank you.

01:13:37.180 --> 01:13:39.348
- That was unbelievable.
- Or the chamomile.

01:13:39.415 --> 01:13:40.950
No kidding, man. No kidding.

01:13:41.017 --> 01:13:42.518
- Mom, where are the cups?
- The cup, it's where..

01:13:42.585 --> 01:13:44.153
Top shelf.

01:13:46.723 --> 01:13:48.124
Oh, my God, I'm so sorry.

01:13:48.191 --> 01:13:49.859
I didn't know this was gonna
end up like this.

01:13:49.926 --> 01:13:53.429
No, I am being hysterical.
I apologize.

01:13:53.496 --> 01:13:55.699
- It's not even funny, mom.
- Did you put him up to this?

01:13:55.765 --> 01:13:57.066
No, I didn't ask him
to steal the car

01:13:57.133 --> 01:13:59.135
but when he had it,
I was all, "Why not?"

01:13:59.202 --> 01:14:01.070
Maybe because
it's completely irrational.

01:14:01.137 --> 01:14:02.305
Look, I knew that
you were never gonna

01:14:02.371 --> 01:14:03.339
let us see each other.

01:14:03.406 --> 01:14:04.540
It was worth the risk.

01:14:04.607 --> 01:14:05.842
God, why would you think that?

01:14:05.909 --> 01:14:07.811
Because you keep him in a cage.
You both do.

01:14:07.877 --> 01:14:09.779
You never let him do
anything fun, ever.

01:14:09.846 --> 01:14:11.114
- Chloe--
- Okay, okay. Take it easy.

01:14:11.180 --> 01:14:13.016
Fantastic,
I'm getting parenting lessons

01:14:13.082 --> 01:14:14.383
from a couple of hippies
and their daughter.

01:14:15.785 --> 01:14:16.753
Uh, maybe you should be
thanking us

01:14:16.820 --> 01:14:18.387
for taking care of Sean

01:14:18.454 --> 01:14:19.856
instead of getting aggressive.

01:14:19.923 --> 01:14:22.025
Listen, I'm happy
that my son is alive and well

01:14:22.091 --> 01:14:25.161
but that's right about
where my gratitude ends.

01:14:25.228 --> 01:14:27.831
Maybe, uh, the kids
should go outside

01:14:27.897 --> 01:14:30.734
for a minute, so that
we can talk, the adults.

01:14:32.301 --> 01:14:33.970
- The kids need to stay.
- The kids need to stay.

01:14:35.604 --> 01:14:37.140
I would prefer if they were here

01:14:37.206 --> 01:14:39.108
because maybe some of us
would act a little more civil.

01:14:39.175 --> 01:14:40.977
That's right, keep an eye on me

01:14:41.044 --> 01:14:43.412
because I might use some words
you're not familiar with.

01:14:43.479 --> 01:14:44.447
- Ooh.
- Wow, wow.

01:14:44.513 --> 01:14:45.481
I just don't think that

01:14:45.548 --> 01:14:47.283
right now is the time to be

01:14:47.350 --> 01:14:48.985
unpacking all of this.

01:14:49.052 --> 01:14:51.520
I mean, it's no mystery
that Sean's in crisis.

01:14:51.587 --> 01:14:54.057
Oh, are you saying
that you can read his mind?

01:14:54.123 --> 01:14:56.092
Well, please tell me,
because I would love to know

01:14:56.159 --> 01:14:58.661
what we've done
that is so atrocious.

01:14:58.728 --> 01:15:01.097
You're suffocating him.

01:15:01.164 --> 01:15:03.632
Did he actually
tell you that or..

01:15:03.699 --> 01:15:05.301
It's clear as day, lady.

01:15:05.368 --> 01:15:07.636
Uh, no, I'm Lisa,
and this is Robert.

01:15:07.703 --> 01:15:10.573
And from what I can tell,
there is no parenting going on

01:15:10.639 --> 01:15:12.842
in this household whatsoever.

01:15:12.909 --> 01:15:14.811
For Paula and Henry

01:15:14.878 --> 01:15:17.113
we respect
Chloe's ideas and needs.

01:15:17.180 --> 01:15:18.447
And the two of you
don't even know

01:15:18.514 --> 01:15:20.016
that Sean is confused
about his future.

01:15:20.083 --> 01:15:21.818
Well, of course, he's confused,
his frontal lobe

01:15:21.885 --> 01:15:23.853
isn't even developed
fully to process

01:15:23.920 --> 01:15:25.154
the consequences of his actions

01:15:25.221 --> 01:15:26.389
which is why
we need to keep him

01:15:26.455 --> 01:15:28.091
on track
despite those limitations.

01:15:28.157 --> 01:15:29.926
There are those big words
you were talking about.

01:15:29.993 --> 01:15:32.195
So, you're saying Sean doesn't
know what's best for him?

01:15:32.261 --> 01:15:34.097
No teenager knows
what's best for them

01:15:34.163 --> 01:15:35.664
and th-tha-tha-that's why
parents are here

01:15:35.731 --> 01:15:39.568
so that we can prevent you from
making irreversible mistakes.

01:15:39.635 --> 01:15:41.504
Oh, you mean
an irreversible mistake

01:15:41.570 --> 01:15:43.106
that gave you both a son?

01:15:43.172 --> 01:15:44.340
You guys were the ones
that were talking about

01:15:44.407 --> 01:15:45.741
having an abortion.

01:15:45.809 --> 01:15:47.310
- Okay, that was never the plan.
- I'm sorry!

01:15:47.376 --> 01:15:49.846
What did you tell him, that you
were thinking of aborting him?

01:15:49.913 --> 01:15:52.215
Jesus Christ! What..

01:15:52.281 --> 01:15:54.050
They were just trying to explain
to me why they gave me up.

01:15:54.117 --> 01:15:55.284
Well, maybe
they shouldn't have told you

01:15:55.351 --> 01:15:57.053
that they were thinking
about killing you.

01:15:57.120 --> 01:15:58.421
They might not have been planned

01:15:58.487 --> 01:16:00.156
but we never ever thought
about abortion.

01:16:00.223 --> 01:16:02.491
Well, then why bring it up?

01:16:02.558 --> 01:16:03.827
It's your lucky day, Sean.

01:16:03.893 --> 01:16:06.029
We didn't kill you,
we just, mm..

01:16:06.095 --> 01:16:07.463
...abandoned you
and kept your sister.

01:16:07.530 --> 01:16:08.932
You've no idea
what you're talking about.

01:16:08.998 --> 01:16:10.499
That's not how it happened.

01:16:10.566 --> 01:16:12.035
Please stop, just go.

01:16:12.101 --> 01:16:13.336
Let me just go back, okay?

01:16:13.402 --> 01:16:14.770
Hey, you're right.
You should just go.

01:16:14.838 --> 01:16:16.172
Sean can decide for himself.

01:16:16.239 --> 01:16:17.106
Yeah, except

01:16:17.173 --> 01:16:18.341
the adults make the decisions

01:16:18.407 --> 01:16:19.175
in my house, okay?

01:16:19.242 --> 01:16:20.476
And if you try to stop me

01:16:20.543 --> 01:16:21.510
I will call my attorney first

01:16:21.577 --> 01:16:22.946
and then the police.

01:16:23.012 --> 01:16:24.948
Oh, no, we are going
to call the police on you.

01:16:25.014 --> 01:16:27.216
You manipulative asshole,
you push Sean around

01:16:27.283 --> 01:16:28.451
and now you're gonna
try the same shit with us--

01:16:28.517 --> 01:16:29.953
Excuse me, have you stopped

01:16:30.019 --> 01:16:32.088
for a second to think
that, you know, considering

01:16:32.155 --> 01:16:33.823
the-the-the medical attention

01:16:33.890 --> 01:16:35.458
the private schools,
me giving him

01:16:35.524 --> 01:16:36.893
basically everything
he's ever wanted.

01:16:36.960 --> 01:16:37.961
The one thing that he can't get

01:16:38.027 --> 01:16:38.995
out of his head is the fact

01:16:39.062 --> 01:16:40.029
that the two people who were

01:16:40.096 --> 01:16:41.464
supposed to love him the most

01:16:41.530 --> 01:16:42.899
abandoned him.

01:16:42.966 --> 01:16:44.200
- Get back in your Tesla.
- That is not fair.

01:16:44.267 --> 01:16:45.768
- And get out of house.
- That is fair.

01:16:45.835 --> 01:16:47.536
You don't deserve Sean,
neither one of you.

01:16:47.603 --> 01:16:50.306
- Get out!
- Any time now.

01:16:50.373 --> 01:16:51.674
What?

01:16:51.740 --> 01:16:53.176
You little bitch!

01:16:53.242 --> 01:16:54.710
You think that you can just
do whatever you want

01:16:54.777 --> 01:16:56.545
because, what, you didn't learn
how to be a grown up?

01:16:56.612 --> 01:16:59.048
Okay, you know what,
do not talk to her like that.

01:16:59.115 --> 01:17:01.317
You have no idea
what it was like losing Sean.

01:17:01.384 --> 01:17:03.619
And what was it like,
losing Sean, exactly?

01:17:03.686 --> 01:17:04.921
Did you just happen to trip

01:17:04.988 --> 01:17:06.522
and accidently put him up
for adoption.

01:17:06.589 --> 01:17:09.325
I mean, the delusion in this
household is just monumental.

01:17:09.392 --> 01:17:11.394
Guys, calm down, you guys
are acting too crazy!

01:17:11.460 --> 01:17:13.729
Chloe, this is your fault,
you brought him here.

01:17:13.796 --> 01:17:14.998
We all know why
teenage boys make

01:17:15.064 --> 01:17:16.799
these kinds of trips,
don't we, Rob?

01:17:16.866 --> 01:17:18.601
Stop acting
like you can't hear him!

01:17:18.667 --> 01:17:19.702
Don't interrupt, Chloe!

01:17:19.768 --> 01:17:21.304
You-you just interrupted her!

01:17:21.370 --> 01:17:22.972
Alright, will you just listen?

01:17:23.039 --> 01:17:24.908
- Little fish..
- No, don't call me little!

01:17:24.974 --> 01:17:26.375
Alright? I'm not little!

01:17:26.442 --> 01:17:28.644
You j-j-jus-just need to listen
to each other for a sec

01:17:28.711 --> 01:17:31.114
instead of screaming and yelling
and saying these awful things!

01:17:31.180 --> 01:17:32.848
We are listening,
they're the ones saying

01:17:32.916 --> 01:17:34.117
terrible things, Sean.

01:17:34.183 --> 01:17:35.451
- There. Tha-that. Right there.
- What?

01:17:35.518 --> 01:17:37.186
- Is what I'm talking about.
- What?

01:17:37.253 --> 01:17:39.788
You are just
embarrassing yourself. Stop!

01:17:39.855 --> 01:17:42.158
You're right,
I am embarrassed

01:17:42.225 --> 01:17:44.860
that my daughter lies to me,
and then she lured you up here

01:17:44.928 --> 01:17:46.662
promising I don't know what.

01:17:46.729 --> 01:17:48.397
And then she hates us for doing

01:17:48.464 --> 01:17:49.933
what we thought
was best for you.

01:17:49.999 --> 01:17:51.400
And you know what, we did..

01:17:51.467 --> 01:17:53.036
We did what we thought
we had to do

01:17:53.102 --> 01:17:54.203
because we didn't think
there was

01:17:54.270 --> 01:17:55.671
any other way to help you.

01:17:55.738 --> 01:17:57.140
But you're okay now, right.

01:17:57.206 --> 01:17:58.942
- It's just, he's okay.
- You're right.

01:17:59.008 --> 01:18:01.110
- I am okay.
- Right?

01:18:01.177 --> 01:18:03.913
Okay, I'm okay
because of my parents.

01:18:03.980 --> 01:18:06.015
My real parents.

01:18:07.850 --> 01:18:09.285
They have loved me

01:18:09.352 --> 01:18:11.554
and taken care of me.
They've been great parents.

01:18:11.620 --> 01:18:14.390
They have been my parents,
because you..

01:18:14.457 --> 01:18:16.459
Because you were too young
an-an-and too poor

01:18:16.525 --> 01:18:19.996
and too whatever
to take care of me.

01:18:20.063 --> 01:18:21.430
Okay, and that's okay, I get it.

01:18:21.497 --> 01:18:22.498
I forgive you.

01:18:23.832 --> 01:18:25.134
You know what, I-I-I'm glad

01:18:25.201 --> 01:18:26.469
this whole thing worked out
the way I did

01:18:26.535 --> 01:18:28.571
because I'm okay..

01:18:28.637 --> 01:18:30.439
...and I wasn't before.

01:18:31.707 --> 01:18:33.109
God, is life perfect now?

01:18:33.176 --> 01:18:34.877
For everybody, it's okay.

01:18:34.944 --> 01:18:37.413
Really, because I am okay.

01:18:37.480 --> 01:18:40.349
And honestly, if I would have to
do this whole thing over again

01:18:40.416 --> 01:18:42.818
I would do it
the exact same way.

01:18:42.885 --> 01:18:47.156
This time I would choose
to have Chloe in my life.

01:18:47.223 --> 01:18:48.958
Because she didn't,
she didn't choose any of this

01:18:49.025 --> 01:18:50.526
just like me.

01:18:53.162 --> 01:18:55.164
Look...taking the car

01:18:55.231 --> 01:18:57.100
and running away was stupid.

01:18:57.166 --> 01:18:59.635
It was a dumb idea.
Really, it was.

01:18:59.702 --> 01:19:01.770
But it was for the better..

01:19:01.837 --> 01:19:03.572
...because I know her now.

01:19:03.639 --> 01:19:05.274
And I didn't fu..

01:19:06.442 --> 01:19:08.911
I'm-I'm gonna keep
talkin' to her.

01:19:08.978 --> 01:19:10.980
Okay, and I want to be able
to keep seeing her

01:19:11.047 --> 01:19:14.350
and honestly, I don't care what
you guys have to say about that

01:19:14.417 --> 01:19:15.618
or you guys...

01:19:15.684 --> 01:19:17.820
because all of you
have been making decisions

01:19:17.886 --> 01:19:19.722
for us for too long.

01:19:19.788 --> 01:19:22.691
Stupid decisions, bad decisions.

01:19:24.994 --> 01:19:28.097
And I'm done.
I want this decision.

01:19:28.164 --> 01:19:31.200
I want my sister.

01:19:31.267 --> 01:19:33.669
If that's what you want,
Sean, then..

01:19:33.736 --> 01:19:36.605
...we are-are fine with that.

01:19:36.672 --> 01:19:37.740
Us too.

01:19:38.641 --> 01:19:39.608
Yeah.

01:19:42.878 --> 01:19:44.547
Listen..

01:19:49.285 --> 01:19:51.487
- Hmm.
- Thank you, guys.

01:19:52.855 --> 01:19:54.490
Thank you for telling me.

01:19:54.557 --> 01:19:57.093
I wanted to know.

01:19:57.160 --> 01:19:59.562
And it's okay. I-I forgive you.

01:19:59.628 --> 01:20:02.565
I just want us to be okay.

01:20:03.632 --> 01:20:04.933
Yeah.

01:20:05.000 --> 01:20:06.502
We're just..

01:20:06.569 --> 01:20:09.738
We're so glad
we got to meet you finally.

01:20:09.805 --> 01:20:11.340
- And, umm..
- Yeah.

01:20:11.407 --> 01:20:14.310
Well, maybe you'll-you'll wanna
get to know us a little better.

01:20:15.444 --> 01:20:18.514
Yeah, man.
Our door is always open.

01:20:18.581 --> 01:20:19.682
Thank you.

01:20:19.748 --> 01:20:21.417
- Yeah.
- Okay.

01:20:21.484 --> 01:20:22.751
Thank you.

01:20:31.694 --> 01:20:33.028
I'm..

01:20:34.230 --> 01:20:36.965
I'm sorry
I put you through this, mom.

01:20:37.032 --> 01:20:38.501
I'm sorry
I put you through this.

01:20:38.567 --> 01:20:41.237
But thank you for coming, okay.

01:20:41.304 --> 01:20:43.339
Thank you both for coming.

01:20:43.406 --> 01:20:45.541
We're just glad to see you, son.

01:20:49.011 --> 01:20:50.313
Can we just go home, please?

01:20:50.379 --> 01:20:52.448
No, no, wa-wai-wait, wait.

01:20:52.515 --> 01:20:54.617
Not until everyone apologizes.

01:20:54.683 --> 01:20:55.718
Chloe, that's fine.

01:20:55.784 --> 01:20:58.454
No. No, it's not fine.

01:20:58.521 --> 01:21:00.323
We are family now,
and I'm not gonna let

01:21:00.389 --> 01:21:02.658
some stupid fight change that.

01:21:20.176 --> 01:21:22.645
I am sorry for my words.

01:21:25.114 --> 01:21:26.081
Thank you.

01:21:26.149 --> 01:21:27.616
I should have thanked you

01:21:27.683 --> 01:21:29.218
for healing him.

01:21:33.222 --> 01:21:34.757
Thank you.

01:21:37.025 --> 01:21:39.195
- Uh, okay.
- Umm..

01:21:45.501 --> 01:21:46.535
Parents!

01:21:48.604 --> 01:21:50.473
Hey.

01:21:50.539 --> 01:21:52.908
Thank you.

01:21:52.975 --> 01:21:54.277
For what?

01:21:54.343 --> 01:21:56.412
Not hating me.

01:21:56.479 --> 01:21:58.281
That'd be kinda impossible.

01:22:00.183 --> 01:22:02.117
I don't know.

01:22:02.185 --> 01:22:04.253
I caused a lot of drama,
didn't I?

01:22:05.188 --> 01:22:06.855
Yeah, you did.

01:22:06.922 --> 01:22:09.024
It was worth it.

01:22:09.091 --> 01:22:10.659
Do you really have to go?

01:22:12.228 --> 01:22:13.229
Hold on.

01:22:13.296 --> 01:22:14.463
- Hey, mom?
- Yeah.

01:22:14.530 --> 01:22:15.298
Dad?

01:22:15.364 --> 01:22:17.666
Is there any chance that maybe

01:22:17.733 --> 01:22:21.304
Chloe could come with us
to Hawaii this year?

01:22:21.370 --> 01:22:23.939
Well, if her parents agree..

01:22:24.006 --> 01:22:25.508
...yeah.

01:22:25.574 --> 01:22:28.177
Hmm, we'd have to pay her way.

01:22:28.244 --> 01:22:30.846
Umm, I think we can do that,
son.

01:22:32.348 --> 01:22:34.683
See? Now, we can surf
the North Shore together.

01:22:35.418 --> 01:22:37.186
- Oh.
- Hmm.

01:22:38.587 --> 01:22:40.723
I think I'm gonna like
having you as a brother.

01:22:41.957 --> 01:22:43.292
Hey.

01:22:45.294 --> 01:22:46.862
I'll see ya.

01:22:55.271 --> 01:22:59.442
So, I take it
I'm grounded forever?

01:22:59.508 --> 01:23:02.411
Well, apparently
that doesn't work anymore.

01:23:04.247 --> 01:23:05.648
You okay?

01:23:06.682 --> 01:23:09.785
Not entirely,
but that's my own fault.

01:23:11.320 --> 01:23:13.689
Um, I don't understand.

01:23:13.756 --> 01:23:16.892
I thought that
I could show you how to be..

01:23:18.261 --> 01:23:20.028
...but that's not fair, is it?

01:23:20.095 --> 01:23:22.331
You've got to find your own way.

01:23:24.066 --> 01:23:26.902
I'm sorry that I treated you
like a little boy.

01:23:30.373 --> 01:23:31.374
You know...

01:23:31.440 --> 01:23:33.075
..your hippy-dippy birth parents

01:23:33.141 --> 01:23:35.611
they actually have a point.

01:23:35.678 --> 01:23:39.047
You should have a choice
in what you do with your time.

01:23:39.114 --> 01:23:40.783
But don't get too excited,
we're not gonna go

01:23:40.849 --> 01:23:42.485
'full blown-out Chloe here'

01:23:42.551 --> 01:23:46.255
but, but I feel like we can
adjust your schedule.

01:23:47.556 --> 01:23:49.325
Does that mean I can skip piano?

01:23:49.392 --> 01:23:50.926
We could..

01:23:50.993 --> 01:23:53.529
...take out the things
that you don't enjoy.

01:23:53.596 --> 01:23:55.764
Except the shelter.

01:23:55.831 --> 01:23:58.066
We're gonna have to sub
in other things

01:23:58.133 --> 01:23:59.568
'but you can choose those two.'

01:23:59.635 --> 01:24:01.804
So, can I have some free time..

01:24:01.870 --> 01:24:03.406
...to waste?

01:24:03.472 --> 01:24:06.241
As long as you don't ditch,
to surf.

01:24:08.711 --> 01:24:10.913
Thanks, mom.
You're the best.

01:24:12.648 --> 01:24:14.450
I'm never admitting
this out loud

01:24:14.517 --> 01:24:18.120
but it's good
to be wrong sometimes.

01:24:18.186 --> 01:24:19.788
I was wrong about Chloe.

01:24:19.855 --> 01:24:23.959
She's a tsunami, inside
a tornado, inside a hurricane..

01:24:24.026 --> 01:24:25.661
...but I love her anyway.

01:24:25.728 --> 01:24:28.897
And I'm glad
she pulled me into her chaos.

01:24:30.366 --> 01:24:33.569
I guess life is pretty good.

01:24:33.636 --> 01:24:35.904
I'm just happy
I survived this weekend.

01:24:35.971 --> 01:24:39.342
And mostly that my friends
weren't around to see it.

